5819%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChristina%20Cassotis%20worked%20in%20consulting%20for%20years%20before%20becoming%20an%20airport%20CEO.%3Cp%3ELaura%20Petrilla%20courtesy%20of%20Pittsburgh%20International%20Airport%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChristina%20Cassotis%20went%20from%20consulting%20to%20leading%20Pittsburgh%20International%20Airport.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20airport's%20CEO%20said%20a%20lot%20happens%20behind%20the%20scenes%20that%20passengers%20don't%20see.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECassotis%20said%20there%20are%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20misconceptions%20about%20airports.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20essay%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Christina%20Cassotis%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20Allegheny%20County%20Airport%20Authority%2C%20which%20operates%20Pittsburgh%20International%20Airport%20and%20Allegheny%20County%20Airport.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20thought%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-controllers-worlds-hardest-jobs-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20at%20an%20airport%3C%2Fa%3E%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20was%20a%20military%20fighter%20pilot%20in%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20and%20then%20got%20recruited%20by%20Pan%20Am%20World%20Airways%2C%20so%20he%20would%20be%20flying%20to%20really%20exciting%20places%20around%20the%20world%20while%20my%20friend's%20parents%20were%20coming%20home%20from%20dinner%20every%20night.%20My%20dad%20was%20in%20Dhaka%2C%20or%20Buenos%20Aires%2C%20or%20Tokyo.%20So%2C%20in%20a%20very%20small%20New%20Hampshire%20town%2C%20I%20had%20this%20big%20view%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20come%20from%20a%20PR%20background%20and%20ended%20up%20working%20at%20Boston's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairports-refuse-tsa-kristi-noem-video-blaming-democrats-for-shutdown-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELogan%20Airport%3C%2Fa%3E%20early%20in%20my%20career%20for%20almost%20five%20years.%20Through%20a%20project%2C%20I%20met%20the%20owner%20of%20a%20consulting%20company%20who%20recruited%20me%2C%20and%20I%20spent%20the%20next%2017%20years%20consulting%20for%20airports%20around%20the%20world.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20I%20was%20very%20focused%20on%20how%20airports%20could%20help%20attract%20more%20airlines%20and%20the%20right%20airlines%2C%20and%20in%20Europe%2C%20I%20was%20really%20focused%20on%20doing%20due%20diligence%20for%20infrastructure%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20I%20got%20recruited%20to%20see%20if%20I'd%20be%20interested%20in%20running%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairports-entering-alfresco-era-architects-stress-flying-aviation-passengers-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPittsburgh%20International%20Airport%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20initially%20said%20no.%20I%20had%20recently%20gotten%20an%20MBA%20from%20MIT%2C%20and%20even%20though%20I%20loved%20consulting%2C%20I%20really%20wanted%20an%20operational%20role.%20And%20I%20really%20wanted%20a%20place%20where%20I%20could%20prove%20the%20thesis%20that%20you%20can%20run%20a%20really%20good%20public%20utility%20like%20a%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20took%20the%20job%2C%20I%20really%20didn't%20come%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpittsburgh-airport-opening-child-care-center-for-employees-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erun%20the%20airport%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20came%20to%20change%20the%20industry%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22432184d4-eefa-432b-8943-ff7d0f15678f%5C%22%3EAn%20airport%20is%20almost%20like%20a%20small%20city%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20average%20days.%20This%20job%20is%20great%20for%20people%20who%20are%20really%20comfortable%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20uncertainty.%20Things%20happen%20every%20day.%20We%20have%20to%20operate%2024%2F7%2C%20365.%20People%20count%20on%20us%20for%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20say%2050%25%20of%20my%20job%20is%20reactive%20and%2050%25%20is%20proactive.%20I%20have%20meetings%20with%20my%20staff%20and%20one-on-ones%20with%20my%20direct%20reports%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20We%20cover%20what%20everyone%20needs%20to%20know%20is%20happening.%20The%20coordination%20and%20dependencies%20are%20no%20joke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20busy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famtrak-versus-flying-train-plane-holiday-travel-less-stressful-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eholiday%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20season%2C%20we%20pay%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20to%20prepping%20for%20winter%20operations%2C%20prepping%20our%20snow%20crews%2C%20making%20sure%20we%20have%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20chemicals%20for%20plowing%20runways%2C%20and%20taking%20care%20of%20roadways%20and%20pedestrian%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20any%20given%20day%2C%20you%20could%20have%20a%20security%20incident%2C%20and%20that%20changes%20the%20tone%20and%20tenor%20of%20the%20day.%20We%20are%20prepared%20for%20lots%20of%20uncertainty%2C%20and%20we%20train%20for%20it%2C%20we%20drill%20for%20it%2C%20and%20we%20have%20communications%20ready%20to%20go%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20plans%20and%20systems%20in%20place%20so%20we%20are%20ready%20for%20every%20scenario.%20We%20have%20our%20own%20fire%20department%20on%20our%20team.%20They%20respond%20every%20day%20to%20probably%20three%20or%20four%20incidents%20that%20could%20be%20lifesaving%20incidents%20in%20the%20terminal.%20It's%20almost%20like%20we're%20a%20small%20city.%20There's%20an%20incredible%20network%20of%20individuals%20who%20are%20ready%20every%20day%20for%20something%20to%20go%20sideways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237d29a2b-8042-4f07-b1c8-d5cd446903a3%5C%22%3EA%20lot%20of%20what%20goes%20on%20at%20airports%20happens%20behind%20the%20scenes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20that%20goes%20on%20that%20passengers%20don't%20see%20or%20notice.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20I%20think%20that's%20a%20credit%20to%20the%20teams%20that%20make%20it%20look%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20running%20an%20entire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fim-an-airport-baggage-handler-heres-what-its-like-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebaggage%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that%20baggage%20system%20has%20to%20work.%20When%20it%20breaks%20down%2C%20then%20our%20field%20maintenance%20crews%20have%20to%20go%20and%20put%20bags%20on%20carts%20and%20help%20the%20airlines%20move%20them%20because%20the%20volume%20is%20too%20big.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20responsible%20for%20plowing%20the%20runways%20and%20keeping%20the%20roadways%20clear%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20that%20the%20grass%20is%20cut%20in%20the%20spring%20and%20summer%20so%20that%20we%20don't%20attract%20wildlife.%20We%20have%20a%20wildlife%20administrator%2C%20because%20you%20can't%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanimals-making-surprising-appearances-at-airports-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewildlife%20in%20an%20airport%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20don't%20want%20birds.%20We%20don't%20want%20people%20feeding%20stray%20cats.%20We%20have%20a%20cybersecurity%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20part%20of%20my%20job%20is%20honestly%20people%20making%20assumptions%20because%20they%20don't%20know%20how%20the%20airport%20operates%20or%20what%20we're%20getting%20done%20every%20day.%20I%20think%20a%20common%20thing%20that%20is%20overlooked%20is%20that%20the%20airport%20is%20actually%20separate%20from%20the%20airlines.%20It's%20its%20own%20entity.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-chaos-airport-worker-quit-industry-low-pay-rude-customers-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAirport%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20get%20to%20fly%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20things%20we%20have%20to%20fix%2C%20but%20not%20everything%20is%20up%20to%20us.%20We%20actually%20don't%20deliver%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20services%20directed%20to%20the%20passengers.%20We%20don't%20fly%20the%20plane.%20We%20don't%20even%20get%20to%20tell%20the%20plane%20where%20to%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20can't%20you%20just%20get%20a%20flight%20to%20a%20specific%20destination%3F%26quot%3B%20To%20which%20I%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20150%20friends%20who%20want%20to%20go%20every%20day%3F%26quot%3B%20That's%20what%20it's%20going%20to%20take.%20We%20actually%20have%20to%20sell%20our%20community%20to%20the%20airlines%2C%20and%20so%20we%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20evaluating%20the%20air%20transportation%20market%20for%20our%20community%20and%20everybody%20we%20compete%20with%20to%20see%20how%20we%20stack%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20my%20job%2C%20and%20I%20like%20thinking%20about%20my%20job.%20Of%20course%2C%20it's%20stressful%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20kind%20of%20stress%20I'm%20built%20for.%20I%20am%20very%20good%20at%20managing%20lots%20of%20complexity.%20I%20really%20love%20understanding%20stakeholders%20and%20what%20they%20need%20and%20how%20to%20communicate%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20constantly%20looking%20for%20better%20ways%20to%20do%20things.%20I%20care%20a%20lot%20about%20making%20sure%20our%20staff%20feels%20engaged.%20Airports%20are%20fun%20places%20to%20work.%20And%20these%20are%20the%20jobs%20I%20don't%20see%20AI%20replacing%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpittsburgh-international-airport-ceo-career-consulting-what-passengers-dont-see-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1766662141000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694b0ab904eda4732f2e124a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpittsburgh-international-airport-ceo-career-consulting-what-passengers-dont-see-2