erested%20in%20the%20business%20side%20of%20technology%2C%20so%20I%20left%20my%20job%20in%20India%20to%20pursue%20an%20MBA%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Arizona.%20My%20goal%20was%20to%20gain%20business%20acumen%20to%20complement%20my%20engineering%20background.%20I%20saw%20firsthand%20how%20much%20innovation%20takes%20place%20in%20the%20US%20and%20how%20many%20opportunities%20exist%20to%20work%20on%20cutting-edge%20products%2C%20which%20inspired%20me%20to%20build%20my%20career%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20valuable%20parts%20of%20the%20MBA%20program%20was%20its%20partnerships%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-job-market-hiring-cracked-layoffs-amazon-microsoft-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20curriculum%2C%20representatives%20from%20Microsoft%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Google%20brought%20projects%20to%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20formed%20teams%2C%20worked%20on%20deliverables%2C%20and%20were%20graded%20by%20company%20representatives.%20In%202016%2C%20I%20was%20team%20lead%20on%20a%20Microsoft%20project%2C%20and%20we%20did%20an%20excellent%20job.%20That%20gave%20me%20a%20chance%20to%20network%20and%20to%20demonstrate%20my%20skills%20to%20an%20actual%20Microsoft%20product%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22063129d1-fc1b-4465-b103-7b3d1d3ee55b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfter%20I%20graduated%2C%20reality%20hit%20hard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20to%20about%20200%20jobs%2C%20sending%20the%20same%20generic%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20without%20referrals.%20I%20received%20only%20three%20calls%20back%20and%20passed%20two%20interviews%2C%20but%20both%20offers%20were%20subsequently%20rescinded%3A%20one%20company%20considered%20my%20visa%20too%20risky%20without%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscis.gov%2Fworking-in-the-united-states%2Fstudents-and-exchange-visitors%2Foptional-practical-training-extension-for-stem-students-stem-opt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESTEM%20extension%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20another%20cited%20budgetary%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20needed%20to%20secure%20a%20job%20within%2060-90%20days%20after%20graduation%2C%20or%20I%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20return%20to%20India.%20I%20ran%20out%20of%20money%2C%20asked%20a%20friend%20if%20I%20could%20crash%20on%20their%20couch%2C%20and%20felt%20a%20constant%20sense%20of%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20I%20stayed%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20Microsoft%20contact%20I'd%20met%20through%20my%20MBA%20project.%20When%20an%20opening%20came%20up%2C%20I%20asked%20if%20he%20would%20refer%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20agreed%2C%20and%20I%20rewrote%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20match%20the%20specific%20role.%20The%20hiring%20manager%20liked%20my%20application%2C%20called%20me%20in%2C%20and%20I%20got%20a%20shot.%20That%20referral%20and%20tailoring%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20made%20all%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-job-optimize-linkedin-profile-jasmine-bortters-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehired%20by%20Microsoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%202017%20and%20started%20as%20a%20product%20manager.%20I%20became%20a%20senior%20product%20manager%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4ac5f3d-8757-4bfc-ac98-d05bf9394e78%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELanding%20a%20job%20in%20Big%20Tech%20isn't%20one%20step%3B%20it's%20two%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20you%20have%20to%20get%20the%20interview%2C%20and%20second%2C%20you%20have%20to%20pass%20it.%20For%20the%20first%20step%2C%20referrals%20are%20critical.%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20receive%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20every%20month.%20A%20referral%20can%20push%20yours%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20stack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prepare%20for%20interviews%2C%20I%20relied%20heavily%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresum