led%20you%20to%20start%20Rocsys%20and%20focus%20on%20automated%20charging%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20previously%20founded%20a%20company%20called%20Epyon%2C%20which%20made%20fast%20chargers%20for%20electric%20cars.%20That%20company%20was%20acquired%20by%20ABB%2C%20and%20I%20spent%20six%20years%20there%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20product%20line%20for%20electric-vehicle%20charging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20final%20year%20at%20ABB%2C%20we%20had%20an%20experience%20that%20was%20somewhat%20unusual%3A%20There%20was%20a%20customer%20from%20San%20Francisco%20who%20bought%20a%20lot%20of%20fast%20chargers%2C%20but%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20tell%20us%20what%20they%20were%20doing%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgm-pulls-robotaxi-bet-cruise-focus-self-driving-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECruise%2C%20the%20self-driving%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20was%20in%202017.%20In%20South%20San%20Francisco%2C%20Cruise%20had%20a%20big%20white-box%20warehouse%20where%20they'd%20built%20a%20complete%20indoor%20test%20track%2C%20because%20they%20didn't%20yet%20have%20a%20permit%20to%20go%20on%20public%20roads.%20The%20vehicle%20would%20drive%20for%20about%20two%20hours%20and%20then%20park%20itself%3B%20a%20person%20would%20then%20walk%20over%20and%20plug%20it%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20triggered%20the%20idea%3A%20If%20you%20take%20out%20the%20human%20driver%2C%20the%20interface%20to%20the%20infrastructure%20is%20actually%20broken.%20If%20you%20want%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-robotaxi-autonomous-vehicles-expansion-plans-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautonomous%20vehicles%20to%20scale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20company%20that%20fixes%20the%20interface%20to%20the%20built%20world%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20charging%2C%20entering%20a%20parking%20garage%2C%20or%20going%20into%20a%20car%20wash.%20All%20the%20infrastructure%20is%20built%20for%20human%20drivers.%20That%20was%20the%20big%20idea%20behind%20Rocsys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20first%20began%20focusing%20more%20on%20ports%20and%20logistics%20yards%20because%2C%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20there%20were%20few%20autonomous%20vehicles%20beyond%20those%20used%20in%20logistics%20operations%20and%20port%20terminals.%20Then%2C%20last%20year%2C%20robotaxis%20became%20mainstream%20in%20the%20US%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20we%20established%20a%20dedicated%20team%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20robotaxi%20market%20in%20the%20US.%20We%20won%20our%20first%20very%20large%20customer%20contract%20in%20robotaxis%20%E2%80%94%20I%20can't%20talk%20about%20it%20publicly%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20are%20about%20to%20sign%20the%20second%20one.%20That%20contract%20is%20for%20automated%20charging%20at%20service%20depots%20for%20robotaxis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERocsys's%20thesis%20is%20that%20manual%20charging%20is%20prone%20to%20errors%2C%20time-consuming%2C%20and%20costly%20to%20operate.%20How%20does%20automated%20charging%20solve%20those%20three%20problems%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20in%20robotaxi%20depots%20in%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20using%20stopwatches%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20time%20each%20task%20takes.%20With%20charging%2C%20you%20walk%20to%20the%20vehicle%2C%20plug%20it%20in%2C%20and%20then%20half%20an%20hour%20later%2C%20you%20walk%20back%20and%20unplug.%20It%20may%20seem%20small%2C%20but%20upon%20examining%20the%20metrics%2C%20it's%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20metrics%20add%20up%20to%20that%201%3A12%20or%201%3A14%20ratio%20of%20vehicles%20per%20head%20count%20in%20the%20depot.%20If%20you%20take%20a%20city%20like%20Los%20Angeles%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwaymo-robotaxi-test-drive-san-francisco-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESan%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20might%20need%20roughly%2010%2C000%20vehicles%20to%20operate%20a%20sizable%20fleet%2C%20which%20means%20you'd%20need%20to%20hire%20roughly%20800%20to%201%2C000%20people%20just%20to%20keep%20that%20fleet%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%2C%20it's%20not%20really%20a%20career.%20This%20job%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20walking%20around%20in%20a%20depot%20outside%2C%20plugging%20a%20vehicle%20in%2C%20and%20wiping%20a%20screen.%20The%20average%20tenure%20is%20about%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hassle%20is%20insane.%20These%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoonshot-ideas-that-became-reality-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etech-savvy%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20building%20autonomous%20vehicles%20need%20to%20establish%20a%20comprehensive%20parallel%20infrastructure%20of%20gig%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20including%20HR%2C%20facilities%2C%20and%20OSHA%20requirements%20%E2%80%94%20everything.%20It%20breaks%20the%20scale%20and%20is%20very%20costly%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20product%20means%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20build%20that%20whole%20parallel%20organization%2C%20which%20is%20a%20complete%20distraction%20from%20their%20core%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20closely%20at%20depot%20operations%2C%20what%20do%20the%20numbers%20behind%20the%20actual%20labor%20look%20like%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlugging%20in%2C%20inspecting%20the%20vehicle%2C%20performing%20a%20quick%20interior%20clean%2C%20and%20then%20walking%20back%20to%20unplug%20lasts%20between%20300%20and%20400%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20interruptions%20in%20between%20because%20charging%20is%20so%20important%20for%20the%20throughput%20of%20the%20depot%20that%20it%20gets%20priority.%20So%2C%20if%20someone%20is%20cleaning%20a%20vehicle%2C%20they%20have%20to%20stop%20when%20a%20new%20one%20arrives%2C%20walk%20over%2C%20plug%20it%20in%2C%20and%20then%20walk%20back.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20inefficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20automate%20charging%2C%20you%20take%20out%20roughly%20half%20the%20head%20count.%20Then%20you%20can%20optimize%20the%20other%20tasks%20so%20they're%20more%20sequential%20instead%20of%20in%20an%20ad-hoc%20manner.%20The%20efficiency%20gains%20are%20huge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20the%20ratio%20for%20current%20depot%20operations%20is%20one%20human%20per%2012%20robotaxis%2C%20then%20what%20does%20the%20ratio%20look%20like%20with%20automated%20chargers%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20cleaning%20and%20inspection%20are%20still%20manual%20processes%2C%20then%20you%20will%20more%20than%20double%20the%20number%20of%20vehicles%20served%20per%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20have%20a%20road%20map%20to%20automate%20those%20other%20processes.%20We're%20currently%20focused%20on%20charging%20because%20that's%20the%20primary%20customer%20request%2C%20but%20we%20have%20developed%20a%20proof%20of%20concept%20for%20automated%20inspection%20and%20have%20already%20built%20a%20working%20system%20for%20automated%20interior%20cleaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20labor-cost%20differences%20between%20a%20depot%20that%20uses%20human%20labor%20versus%20a%20depot%20with%20Rocsys%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20savings%20range%20from%2030%25%20to%2070%25%20in%20the%20first%20year%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20dynamics%20of%20each%20depot.%20It's%20really%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20couple%20years%20ago%2C%20there%20was%20some%20buzz%20around%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-tesla-is-building-a-wild-car-charger-that-automatically-comes-out-of-the-wall-and-connects-to-your-car-like-a-solid-metal-snake-2014-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETesla's%20robot%20charger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20What's%20to%20stop%20Tesla%20from%20reviving%20that%20idea%20and%20doing%20automated%20charging%20themselves%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ceo-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20do%20everything%20himself%2C%20so%20they%20might.%20It%20would%20make%20a%20ton%20of%20sense%20for%20them.%20The%20whole%20pitch%20for%20Tesla%20is%20that%20it%20can%20upgrade%20the%20entire%20fleet%20to%20robo%C2%ADtaxis%2C%20and%20those%20vehicles%20need%20to%20be%20charged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20upgrade%20a%20couple%20of%20million%20Teslas%20to%20be%20autonomously%20driven%2C%20they%20need%20an%20automated%20charging%20option.%20So%20I%20think%20it%20would%20be%20very%20logical%20for%20them%20to%20bring%20robotic%20charging%20to%20market.%20It's%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20captive%20model.%20Tesla%20has%20pitched%20inductive%20(wireless)%20charging%20for%20the%20dedicated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-elon-musk-fan-robotaxi-event-experiences-cybercab-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETesla%20robotaxi%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20robotaxi%20fleets%20don't%20have%20that.%20None%20of%20the%20vehicles%20have%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20before%20we%20even%20talk%20about%20robotaxis%20scaling%2C%20doesn't%20the%20US%20still%20have%20issues%20with%20its%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-vehicle-range-ev-charging-station-infrastructure-issues-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEV%20charging%20infrastructure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20that%20need%20to%20be%20solved%20first%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20for%20the%20robotaxi%20use-case%2C%20it's%20sort%20of%20a%20parallel%20world%20because%20the%20charging%20stations%20are%20very%20dedicated%20to%20a%20fleet.%20So%2C%20robotaxi%20operators%20build%20out%20their%20fleets%2C%20but%20in%20parallel%2C%20they%20also%20develop%20the%20charging%20infrastructure%20with%20partners%20or%20independently.%20It's%20sort%20of%20bespoke%20to%20the%20robotaxi%20operation.%20Currently%2C%20the%20hubs%20are%20dedicated%20to%20one%20operator%20%E2%80%94%20Waymo%20has%20its%20own%20hubs%2C%20while%20Zoox%20has%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20differ%20from%20public%20charging%20infrastructure%2C%20so%20I'd%20say%20they%20are%20parallel%20worlds.%20There's%20no%20reason%20to%20solve%20one%20problem%20before%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20robo%C2%ADtaxis%20scaling%20fast%20enough%20today%20for%20Rocsys%20to%20build%20a%20real%20business%20on%20automated%20charging%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbsolutely.%20Over%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20we%20can%20expect%20a%20substantial%20market%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobotaxis%20are%20a%20limited%20fleet%2C%20but%20usage%20is%20extremely%20intense.%20The%20vehicles%20are%20running%2024%2F7%2C%20three%20to%20four%20times%20per%20day.%20There%20is%20already%20a%20substantial%20market%20for%20us%2C%20with%20a%20fleet%20of%20several%20thousand%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ratio%20of%20vehicles%20to%20charging%20bays%20%E2%80%94%20the%20parking%20spots%20where%20a%20vehicle%20can%20be%20charged%20%E2%80%94%20is%20about%20one%20to%20six.%20For%206%2C000%20vehicles%2C%20you%20need%20around%201%2C000%20charging%20bays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20information%20suggests%20that%20there%20are%20somewhere%20between%203%2C000%20and%204%2C000%20robotaxis%20on%20US%20roads%2C%20if%20you%20add%20up%20Waymo%2C%20Zoox%2C%20and%20others.%20That%20means%20the%20current%20market%20is%20a%20few%20thousand%20bays%20to%20serve%2C%20which%20is%20already%20a%20very%20nice%20starting%20market.%20But%20it's%20scaling%20so%20fast%20now.%20There's%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdave-ferguson-nuro-uber-lucid-robotaxi-san-francisco-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUber-Nuro%20announcement%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%2020%2C000-vehicle%20robo%C2%ADtaxi%20fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20we're%20seeing%20now%20already%20feels%20like%20a%20land-grab%20dynamic.%20There's%20Waymo%2C%20there's%20Zoox.%20Tesla%20%E2%80%94%20let's%20see%20how%20far%20they%20actually%20are.%20There's%20also%20Nuro%20and%20Uber.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwayve-tesla-full-self-driving-comparison-adas-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWayve%20from%20the%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20also%20pretty%20impressive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20really%20feels%20like%20a%20land%20grab%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20you%20approaching%20Uber%2C%20Lyft%2C%20and%20all%20the%20other%20players%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20be%20sure%20that%20we%20talk%20to%20every%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20will%20you%20be%20able%20to%20announce%20your%20first%20big%20robotaxi%20customer%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20have%20a%20date%20yet%2C%20but%20I'm%20fairly%20certain%20it'll%20be%20sometime%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobotaxi-bottleneck-ev-charging-infrastructure-automation-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1766654041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694af67264858d02d217572f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobotaxi-bottleneck-ev-charging-infrastructure-automation-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rocsys%20CEO%20Crijn%20Bouman%20is%20making%20automated%20charging%20ports%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20doubling%20the%20amount%20of%20robotaxis%20that%20can%20be%20managed%20by%20a%20single%20human.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobotaxi-bottleneck-ev-charging-infrastructure-automation-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Ajit%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20given%